      <Table>
        <TableRowGroup>
          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>MergeLocalizationDirectives Task</Run>

              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

        </TableRowGroup>

      </Table>

      <Paragraph><Run Foreground="DarkGray">[The content included in this documentation is a sub-set of the Windows SDK, and may not be complete or current. Please see the online Windows SDK for current documentation.]</Run>

      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph/>
      <Paragraph>The <Run FontWeight="Bold">MergeLocalizationDirectives</Run>
 task merges the localization attributes and comments of one or more binary XAML (BAML) files into a single file for the whole assembly.    
      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph FontSize="22">Attributes    
      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph><Run FontWeight="Bold"/>
      </Paragraph>

      <Table>
        <TableRowGroup>
          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph>Parameter             
              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph>Description             
              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>GeneratedLocalizationFiles</Run>

              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph>Required <Run FontWeight="Bold">ITaskItem[]</Run>
 parameter.            
              </Paragraph>

              <Paragraph>Specifies the list of localization directives files for individual BAML files.            
              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>OutputFile</Run>

              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph>Required <Run FontWeight="Bold">String</Run>
 output parameter.            
              </Paragraph>

              <Paragraph>Specifies the output path of the compiled localization directives assembly.            
              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

        </TableRowGroup>

      </Table>

      <Paragraph FontSize="22">Remarks    
      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph>Localization attributes and comments can be configured by developers in Extensible Application Markup Language (XAML) content. Using Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF) localization support, it is possible to strip out localization attributes and comments and place them into a file (a <Run FontWeight="Bold">.loc</Run>
 file) that is separate from the generated assembly. This can be achieved by using the <Run FontWeight="Bold">LocalizationPropertyStorage</Run>
 attribute. For more information on localization attributes and comments, and <Run FontWeight="Bold">LocalizationPropertyStorage</Run>
, see <Hyperlink NavigateUri="ead2d9ac-b709-4ec1-a924-39927a29d02f.xaml">Localization Attributes and Comments</Hyperlink>
.    
      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph FontSize="22">Example    
      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph>The following example merges the localization comments of several BAML files into a single <Run FontWeight="Bold">.loc</Run>
 file.    
      </Paragraph>

      <Table>
        <TableRowGroup>
          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run/>
              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph TextAlignment="Left" FontSize="8pt" FontFamily="Courier New" xml:space="preserve"><Run>
&lt;Project xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/developer/msbuild/2003"> 
&lt;UsingTask TaskName="Microsoft.Build.Tasks.Windows.MergeLocalizationDirectives" AssemblyFile="C:\Program Files\Reference Assemblies\Microsoft\WinFx\v3.0\PresentationBuildTasks.dll" /> 
&lt;Target Name="MergeLocalizationDirectivesTask"> 
&lt;MergeLocalizationDirectives GeneratedLocalizationFiles="obj\debug\page1.baml;obj\debug\page2.baml;obj\debug\page3.baml" OutputFile="obj\debug\WPFMSBuildSample.loc" /> 
&lt;/Target> 
&lt;/Project></Run>
            
              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

        </TableRowGroup>

      </Table>

